The units of this expression are $(	ext{dimensionless}) / ((	ext{erg}\,	ext{s}) \cdot 	ext{dimensionless}) = (	ext{erg}\,	ext{s})^{-1}$. This is equivalent to $	ext{erg}^{-1}\,	ext{s}^{-1}$, which is $	ext{erg}^{-1}\,	ext{Hz}$. Since photons are a dimensionless count, this matches the requested units of photons $\mathrm{erg}^{-1}\,\mathrm{Hz}$.

